                    )</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945v08</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d203</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">203</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-08-25T13:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-08-25T13:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-25T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-25T13:00:00-05:00" n="203" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d203">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.51/8–1845: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Greece</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-25T14:00:00-04:00">August 25, 1945—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>869. Your 866 and 867.<note n="61" xml:id="d203fn61">Latter not printed; for
                        summary, see footnote 60, <ref target="#pg_234">p. 234</ref>.</note> While
                    the Export-Import Bank may make moderate loans to aid in the reconstruction of
                    Greece there is no basis for astronomical expectations. The figure named by
                    Varvaressos, 250 million dollars, represents official request presented to the
                    Export-Import Bank Aug 20; but Greek Embassy has been informed by the Bank that
                    question must be presented to full Bank Board and no indication can be given as
                    to when Board will act or what amount if any may be approved.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
